    {
      "id": 8,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "Known Issues — Requires Follow-up",
      "gridPos": {"h": 7, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 32},
      "options": {
        "mode": "html",
        "content": "<div style=\"display:flex;gap:16px;padding:4px\"><div style=\"flex:1;background:#1a0f0f;border:1px solid #F2495C44;border-radius:6px;padding:12px\"><div style=\"color:#F2495C;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px;margin-bottom:8px\">🔴 auto-pentest — Avg 0.293 (Refusing / Wrong Format)</div><div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#ccc;line-height:1.6\">Nearly all prompts returned in 1–22s with 0–1 headers and composite 0.10–0.30. The model routed by auto-pentest is either refusing security-offensive prompts or producing a format incompatible with the rubric scorer. Average time of 11s confirms early natural termination, not truncation. <strong>Action:</strong> probe auto-pentest workspace directly to identify the model + check its system prompt alignment with the rubric header format.</div></div><div style=\"flex:1;background:#1a1200;border:1px solid #FF983044;border-radius:6px;padding:12px\"><div style=\"color:#FF9830;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px;margin-bottom:8px\">⚠️ auto-purpleteam-exec — Avg 0.516 (Agentic Loop, No Structured Output)</div><div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#ccc;line-height:1.6\">Many prompts ran 200–410s with composite=0.10 and 0/N headers — the model is entering its tool-use/agentic execution loop and returning execution artifacts rather than structured markdown. When it does produce prose (lateral_movement, ssrf, linux_privesc, container_escape, api_security_chain) it scores 0.90–1.00. <strong>Action:</strong> add rubric output constraint to auto-purpleteam-exec persona/workspace system prompt, or run scoring pass on tool call outputs separately.</div></div><div style=\"flex:1;background:#0a1a0a;border:1px solid #73BF6944;border-radius:6px;padding:12px\"><div style=\"color:#73BF69;font-weight:bold;font-size:14px;margin-bottom:8px\">✅ Streaming / Timeout — Fixed</div><div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#ccc;line-height:1.6\">Previous run: kernel_exploit_chain took <strong>11,597s</strong>. This run: <strong>89–113s</strong>. Event-driven content-completion stop (all required headers + word_min + MITRE satisfied) combined with max_tokens=6000 backstop eliminated runaway generation. Zero timer dependencies remain in the evaluation path.</div></div></div>"
      }
    }
